# Per-environment tfvars are RENDERED from the LandingZone spec
# (environments/<env>.yaml is the source of truth) by `llz render`, and
# regenerated in CI before every terraform op (the terraform-init composite runs
# `llz render --tfvars-only`). They are transient build artifacts — NOT committed
# — so a spec edit produces one reviewable diff (the spec) instead of two, and a
# rendered-but-unformatted tfvars can never trip the pre-commit `tofu fmt -check`.
#
# Matches cluster/<env>.tfvars, cluster-bootstrap/<env>.tfvars,
# object-storage/<env>.tfvars, and vpc/<network>.tfvars. The committed
# terraform.tfvars.example defaults stay tracked (they end in .example, not
# .tfvars). A working `llz` is therefore required for any terraform op — see
# docs/landing-zone-spec.md.
#
# Legacy (pre-spec) instances never run `llz render`, so they never receive this
# file; their hand-authored <env>.tfvars stay tracked as the source of truth.
*/*.tfvars
